replies.body:
I must agree, it is impossible for a bronze player to dodge most of Syndra's abilities.

I'm not talking about 'bronze - 'bronze' I am talking about people who actually belong in bronze and aren't climbing out, because it is seriously easy to climb out. To be completely honest with you, I was hoping to be placed in bronze 5 because it is so much fun. Not to be an elitist or anything, but people who do belong in bronze are unable to dodge MOST abilities in the game, while also having to worry about farming and map awareness. 

But I know you are asking right now, "Subject 5, How do you beat a Syndra in lane?" I am so glad that you asked this and definitely not me forcing the words into your mouth just then. How do you beat her? Stay out of her Q range, use abilities to farm and punish her for being aggressive- she is very weak against mobility and weak against long range champions. So you want to pick champions like:

{{champion:238}} {{champion:7}} {{champion:101}} {{champion:131}} {{champion:31}} {{champion:12}} {{champion:103}} {{champion:8}} {{champion:43}} {{champion:112}} 

Champions you don't want to pick against her: {{champion:1}} {{champion:84}}
